about.summary: The KEA format provides an implementation of the GDAL specification within the the HDF5 file format.

name: kealib
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.4.6" %}

package:
    name: kealib
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: kealib-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    url: https://bitbucket.org/chchrsc/kealib/downloads/kealib-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    md5: 789174bd519736ac1e726613b6eb7672

build:
    number: 2
    features:
        - vc9  # [win and py27]
        - vc10  # [win and py34]
        - vc14  # [win and py35]

requirements:
    build:
        - toolchain
        - python  # [win]
        - cmake
        - hdf5 1.8.17*

    run:
        - hdf5 1.8.17*

about:
    home: kealib.org
    license: MIT
    summary: The KEA format provides an implementation of the GDAL specification within the the HDF5 file format.

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - gillins
